Freight transport (MHD) will introduce the chip into their ticket system on Wednesday
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be included in the history of the Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragoise Transportation Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will ride the subway, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, it is accessible for about a hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a coupon 30 days or 90 days (the coupon will be valid from 1 January 2009) and have it recorded on their credit card at the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Transportation Agency), located at the Metro Stations Museum, MČstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons via the Internet on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people benefited from the service during the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can permanently forget the windows in the metro stations, where they had to track impatience in long queues in order to obtain paper tickets.
In fact, they will buy their coupon online and will register it on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is at the disposal of passengers a window with trained staff, which will help those interested with the purchase via the internet and will also record the coupon they bought on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Next to the libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, recalling the machines to compose tickets and passengers may have already noticed them in the Roztyly, Budějovicá, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
An automatic will control the coupon instead of the driver
Automatics that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Simply enter the Opencard chip card and the coupon previously purchased will save itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also around the city.
In the peri-urban trains and the 300 to 499 bus lines, mainly used by the inhabitants of the municipalities of the Central Bohème to access the capital.
